  "prompt": "What is the lowest temperature to leave a thermostat so that the pipes don't freeze?",
  "response": "To prevent pipes from freezing, it's recommended to keep your thermostat set no lower than 55\u00b0F (13\u00b0C) when you're away from home during cold weather. If you live in an extremely cold climate, you might want to set it slightly higher, around 60\u00b0F (16\u00b0C). Additionally, you can take other precautions like:\n\n1. Insulating pipes in unheated areas\n2. Letting faucets drip slightly during extreme cold\n3. Opening cabinet doors to allow warm air to circulate around pipes\n4. Sealing air leaks around windows and doors\n\nThe exact temperature can vary depending on your home's insulation, pipe location, and local climate.",
